# PR-B §1.6 — service-role allowlist for the agent runtime.
#
# Files in apps/web-platform/{server,lib} that legitimately import
# `createServiceClient` or `getServiceClient`. The CI grep gate
# (.github/workflows/ci.yml, "service-role-allowlist-gate" job)
# rejects any other importer.
#
# CODEOWNERS pins this file: @jeanderuelle approval is required to add
# a path. Without this, an attacker-modeled PR could add a service-role
# import AND its allowlist line in one commit and the gate would pass.
#
# Format: one path per line, RELATIVE TO REPO ROOT (not apps/web-platform).
# Comments and blank lines are ignored by the gate.
#
# Each path declares one of:
#   - PERMANENT: legitimate by design (auth-domain RPC, signature-
#     verified webhook, bulk sweep with no per-tenant key, etc.)
#   - TRANSITIONAL: enumerated in a follow-up PR's spec; remove the
#     line when that PR migrates the call sites.

# ── Permanent service-role surface ────────────────────────────────────

# Defines `createServiceClient` / `getServiceClient`. The functions
# themselves must reside somewhere; this is the canonical home.
apps/web-platform/lib/supabase/service.ts

# Thin re-export shim (`export { ... } from "./service"`). Historical
# import path; new code should import from `./service` directly.
apps/web-platform/lib/supabase/server.ts

# Tenant-client factory. Uses service-role only for the auth-domain
# `precheck_jwt_mint` RPC (rate-limit + jti generation). Tenant data
# reads/writes go through `createTenantClient(jwt)` (per PR-B §1.1).
apps/web-platform/lib/supabase/tenant.ts

# BYOK lease — reads `api_keys` via tenant-scoped client INSIDE the
# lease body. Service-role here is for the auth-domain RPC plumbing
# (`mintFounderJwt` chain). Lease never bypasses RLS for tenant data.
apps/web-platform/server/byok-lease.ts

# Bulk sweeps in agent-runner.ts at `cleanupOrphanedConversations`
# and `startInactivityTimer`. Both are staleness-keyed
# (`last_active < cutoff`) — no per-tenant key, no userId in scope.
# `getFreshTenantClient(userId)` is structurally inapplicable
# (per type-design F2 + architecture F1). The user-scoped sites in
# the same file MUST migrate (per spec tasks §1.5.1).
apps/web-platform/server/agent-runner.ts

